Graphical parameters in R with par(): With great power comes great responsibility

library(compbio4all)

Save plotting defaults

par_defaults <- par()

Data

census <- 1:39
year.t   <- 1959:1997
females.N <- c(44,47,46,44,46,
               45,46,40,39,39,
               42,39,41,40,33,
               36,34,39,35,34,
               38,36,37,41,39,
               51,47,57,48,60,
               65,74,69,65,57,
               70,81,99,99)
lambda.i <- females.N[-1]/females.N[-length(females.N)]
lambda.i <- c(lambda.i,NA)
lambda_log <- log(lambda.i)
bear_N <- data.frame(census,
                year.t,
                females.N,
                lambda.i, 
                lambda_log)

A single-panel plot - default

plot(females.N ~ year.t, data = bear_N)

A single-panel plot - explicitly with par()

par(mfrow = c(1,1))
plot(females.N ~ year.t, data = bear_N)
